profile.bio: After his breakthrough role in “The Talented Mr. Ripley” (1999), Jude Law landed on the Hollywood scene and quickly began to turn audiences with his incredible performances. He starred in Steven Spielberg’s “A.I. Artificial Intelligence” (2001), “Road to Perdition” (2002), “Cold Mountain” (2003), “Closer” (2004), “The Aviator” (2004), and “Alfie” (2004). A truly prolific performer, Jude Law starred as Dr. Watson in “Sherlock Holmes” (2009) and “Sherlock Holmes: A Game of Shadows” (2011). He played a young Albus Dumbledore in “Fantastic Beasts: The Crimes of Grindelwald” (2018) and the sequel “Fantastic Beasts: The Secrets of Dumbledore” (2022). He has played a role in both the Star Wars universe, “Star Wars: Skeleton Crew” (2024), and the MCU by starring in “Captain Marvel” (2019). Jude Law is an acclaimed actor who has worked with a series of incredible directors, such as Wes Anderson’s “The Grand Budapest Hotel” (2014), Martin Scorsese’s “Hugo” (2011), Wong Kar-wai’s “My Blueberry Nights” (2007), Steven Soderbergh’s “Contagion” (2011), and countless others. While mostly an actor for the big screen, he has starred in TV shows such as “The Young Pope” (2016) and follow-up show “The New Pope” (2020) and “Black Rabbit” (2025), a show he also executive produced.
